results.description:
We are happy to announce our first Blockchain meetup hosted with nexussquared in Warsaw. The goal is to share great projects among the blockchain community and introduce you to the first blockchain start-up acceleration programme in Europe.

Taking a novel approach to fostering startups, nexuslab introduces a programme inspired by the blockchain paradigms of decentralisation, trust and efficiency. To extend the range and expertise of its mentor network, the programme will collaborate with Startupbootcamp Fintech.

Applications can be registered via <a>https://www.f6s.com/nexuslab </a>;;

Meetup Speaker:


Daniel Gasteiger

Daniel has worked in financial services for more than 20 years and is the co-founder nexussquared, a blockchain business platform in Zurich / Switzerland.

nexussquared Zurich

nexussquared is the first blockchain business platform in continental Europe, based in Zurich / Switzerland and looks to build on top of the exsiting ecosystem in Switzerland called Crypto-Valley Zug. We have great companies based there, among others Ethereum, Xapo and Monetas and look to attract start-ups to build with us great products on the basis of that ecosystem. 

Venue will be announced shortly!
results.name: First Blockchain Wizards meetup

Zapraszamy do zgłaszania swoich tematów :-)

Pozdrawiamy,

Bartłomiej Twardowski

Radosław Kita

results.description:
Free Workshop: Doing business in Poland - Law & Practice

Hosted by Warsaw Business Network

Are you a business owner that would like to learn more about the laws and practices in Poland? Or maybe you are thinking about quitting your job and starting that million dollar ideas you've been sitting. Before you make your next big move in the business world, make sure you understand the basics.

During the workshop you will learn:

- How to set up a business / Polish company;
- How to find risks in Polish contracts;
- How to negotiate with the Polish counter-parties.

Who should sign up?

If you are a manager or business owner who only starts the business activities in Poland and wants to understand the local business environment - this workshop is for you.

This event will be held in English, but the speaker will happily accept questions in Polish during the question and answer section.

***About the Speaker****

Website 

Facebook Page 

Joanna Mamczur is an attorney-at-law in Warsaw. For several years she has been advising her Polish and international Clients in cooperation with leading law firms in the field of commercial law.

Joanna Mamczur works in Polish, English, French and German.

Her expertise in legal advisory services includes, amongst others, Corporate Law, Mergers and Acquisitions, Banking & Finance and commercial contracts. She also advises in the field of Capital Markets, electronic payment instruments, investment funds and other finance issues subject to the regulatory supervision. Joanna Mamczur currently cooperates with a prominent international law firm which gathers renown experts in commercial law in 13 countries of the CEE/SEE region.
results.name: Free Workshop: Doing business in Poland - Law & Practice
